1. artifact 
2. deployment (i guess widget exists)
3. test results
column5: About Artiactory, deployment, and test results
column11:
193826439 Can someone respond to this one please... 
 softwareklinic
193829797 Please see the Hygieia 2.0 documentation for reference: https://github.com/capitalone/Hygieia/blob/master/Hygieia2.md

Test Results:
- If you publish (via Jenkins hygieia plugin) the cucumber test results, you can select those jenkins jobs in your Quality widget: Functional Test: 
  ![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6014941/13606509/287695ee-e51a-11e5-8379-e19aabb8fed2.png)

Deployment:
The widget already exist. Again, if you publish your deployment results via Jenkins plugin, they will show up in the deployment widget:

![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6014941/13606605/8b34982a-e51a-11e5-820b-054129189adb.png)

Artifacts:
There is no separate widget for Artifact. However, if you publish Artifact info via Jenkins plugin, Hygieia will successfully link your code -> build -> artifact -> deployment "pipeline" in the Hygieia 2.0 product dashboard (see Hygieia 2.0 documentation)

column2:
With Hygieia 2.0, you can publish Build, Sonar Analysis, Artifact Info, Deployment (if using Jenkins to deploy), Cucumber Test Results from Jenkins to Hygieia. Use the latest Jenkins Plugin (https://github.com/capitalone/Hygieia/tree/master/hygieia-jenkins-plugin).

For Github webhook, the  payload url should be set to: http://hygieia-base-url/api/commit/github/v3
Select to publish just the "push" events. 

With the above two new features, you will not need to run github collector, jenkins build collector, sonar collector and jenkins cucumber test collector.

190531129 So we need API, mongodb, and UI with Jenkins plugin?

Sent from my iPhone

On Feb 29, 2016, at 10:01 PM, tabladrum <notifications@github.com<mailto:notifications@github.com>> wrote:

With Hygieia 2.0, you can publish Build, Sonar Analysis, Artifact Info, Deployment (if using Jenkins to deploy), Cucumber Test Results from Jenkins to Hygieia. Use the latest Jenkins Plugin (https://github.com/capitalone/Hygieia/tree/master/hygieia-jenkins-plugin).

For Github webhook, the payload url should be set to: http://hygieia-base-url/api/commit/github/v3
Select to publish just the "push" events.

With the above two new features, you will not need to run github collector, jenkins build collector, sonar collector and jenkins cucumber test collector.

—

column2:
i am trying to set up an instance of Hygieia 2.0.0 but my UI is displaying that there is a Connectivity issue.

> I run mongo at port 27017.
> I run api-2.0.0.jar at port 8080. I can go to localhost:8080/api/dashboard and it returns [ ]
> I run UI with gulp serve and this launches at port 3000.

When I navigate to localhost:3000 I see a red 'x' next to API connectivity. 
Gulp is printing the following line on the terminal:
 `[Proxy] { [Error: getaddrinfo ENOTFOUND] code: 'ENOTFOUND', errno: 'ENOTFOUND', syscall: 'getaddrinfo' }`

Why is the api not connecting with the UI? My mongo instance is successfully connecting with the api.jar
column5: API Connectivity issue with 2.0.0
column11:
190769838 I realized I couldn't ping localhost so I found that the issue was my /etc/hosts file needed to have the line `127.0.0.1 localhost.localdomain localhost`

This solved my issue with getting 2.0.0 working. The api and UI are not connected

java.lang.NullPointerException: null
        at com.capitalone.dashboard.repository.EmbeddedMongoDBRule$SystemProxy.createProxy(EmbeddedMongoDBRule.java:58) ~[test-classes/:na]

        at de.flapdoodle.embed.process.store.CachingArtifactStore.checkDistribution(CachingArtifactStore.java:62) [de.flapdoodle.embed.process-1.50.0.jar:na]

        at org.junit.rules.ExternalResource$1.evaluate(ExternalResource.java:46) [junit-4.11.jar:na]
        at org.junit.rules.RunRules.evaluate(RunRules.java:20) [junit-4.11.jar:na]
        at org.junit.runners.ParentRunner.run(ParentRunner.java:309) [junit-4.11.jar:na]
        at org.springframework.test.context.junit4.SpringJUnit4ClassRunner.run(SpringJUnit4ClassRunner.java:163) [spring-test-4.1.7.RELEASE.jar:4.1.7.RELEASE]
        at org.apache.maven.surefire.junit4.JUnit4Provider.execute(JUnit4Provider.java:264) [surefire-junit4-2.17.jar:2.17]
        at org.apache.maven.surefire.junit4.JUnit4Provider.executeTestSet(JUnit4Provider.java:153) [surefire-junit4-2.17.jar:2.17]
        at org.apache.maven.surefire.junit4.JUnit4Provider.invoke(JUnit4Provider.java:124) [surefire-junit4-2.17.jar:2.17]
        at org.apache.maven.surefire.booter.ForkedBooter.invokeProviderInSameClassLoader(ForkedBooter.java:200) [surefire-booter-2.17.jar:2.17]
        at org.apache.maven.surefire.booter.ForkedBooter.runSuitesInProcess(ForkedBooter.java:153) [surefire-booter-2.17.jar:2.17]
        at org.apache.maven.surefire.booter.ForkedBooter.main(ForkedBooter.java:103) [surefire-booter-2.17.jar:2.17]

This is caused by an assumption in EmbeddedMongoDBRule.java that assumes the HTTP_PROXY URL has a userinfo portion:

```
            URL proxyUrl = new URL(proxy);

            // Case for Proxy authentication required
            try {
                StringTokenizer tokenizedUrl = new StringTokenizer(proxyUrl
                        .**getUserInfo**().toString(), ":");
                if (tokenizedUrl.hasMoreTokens()) {
```

The userinfo portion of the proxy URL is optional, so without it we pop the NPE.

This error is back when trying to run:
mvn sonar:sonar -Dsonar.host.url=http://$(docker-machine ip default):9000 -Dsonar.jdbc.url="jdbc:h2:tcp://$(docker-machine ip default)/sonar"

```
       [ERROR] Failed to execute goal org.sonarsource.scanner.maven:sonar-maven-plugin:3.0.1:sonar (default-cli) on project Hygieia: Unable to read /Users/jaz/work/Hygieia/api/target/jacoco.exec: Incompatible version 1007. -> [Help 1]
```

I did see a comment on a ticket that the version of Jacoco was purposefully moved back to 0.7.5.xxx

I tried 0.7.6.201602180812 (new version, but I still get this error).

I found this ticket on jacoco: https://github.com/jacoco/jacoco/issues/315  bottom line is: "This is not a bug on JaCoCo side, but intentional change for binary dump file as consequence of #310 - see changelog http://www.eclemma.org/jacoco/trunk/doc/changes.html
Third-party integrations, which use this binary dump file (such as SonarQube) should be updated, or previous version of JaCoCo should be used for them."

**I created a issue for the sonar team: https://github.com/SonarSource/sonar-maven/issues/4

Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHubhttps://github.com/capitalone/Hygieia/issues/362#issuecomment-187970933.
 softwareklinic
217782164 I am using latest version of Hygieia and facing same issue of Forbidden access with GitHub private repository. Is there way to solve this??
 bhoslepu
218020547 Hi,
You need to add in your UserID and API key in application .properites file like below.

github.UserId=p710231
github.key=XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXc1

Then modify DefaultGitHubClient.java and force the response string to fetch the password from properties file

```
                            //ResponseEntity<String> response = makeRestCall(queryUrlPage, settings.getUserId(), decryptedPassword);
                            ResponseEntity<String> response = makeRestCall(queryUrlPage, settings.getUserId(), settings.getKey());
```

Thanks,
 ghost
218093283 Thanks.. Its working now. Only thing I have to declare function for getUserId.

column2:
We need to add containers for these collectors to finish the docker setup.  We should create them and also add optional test servers that we can use for demo and automated testing (test servers are under $ROOT/docker, today there is a jenkins and a sonar server you can optionally build for testing).

I plan to add them to the compose file commented out, people can enable them by adding them to their override file.

product-product-collector (this looks empty right now, so now action)
stash-scm-collector
subversion-scm-collector
udeploy-deployment-collector
versionone-feature-collector

205342554 @gitfan89 , It appears that two things are going on here which would affect your error response:
- You are receiving a 403 HTTP response, meaning that your SSL certificate keystore has not been updated correctly with your remove Jira instance
- You still have some property configuration issues

For the first issue, please ensure that you 1) can reach the Jira instance via HTTPS from your Hygieia region and 2) ensure that your Java & OS-level keystore has been updated with the Jira certificate correctly.  To do this, try to telnet or cURL from your Hygieia server to the Jira server - failures would indicate a network firewall or security issue.  Secondly, use openssh or Java Keytool to validate your Java keystore for the Jira certificate presence; also be sure to add the certificate to your OS-level keystore to ensure no break in communication for Linux/Unix systems (the method for OS-level certificate keystore updating is different between each distribution).

Regarding issue 2, see below for an updated/cleaned property file list based on what you have provided me in the text file; please replace your property file with the fixed one below (update with your credentials, etc.):

# Jira Connection Details - Proxy is NOT just a 'Jira specific proxy' - this is your global enterprise proxy

205342554 @gitfan89 , It appears that two things are going on here which would affect your error response:
- You are receiving a 403 HTTP response, meaning that your SSL certificate keystore has not been updated correctly with your remove Jira instance
- You still have some property configuration issues

For the first issue, please ensure that you 1) can reach the Jira instance via HTTPS from your Hygieia region and 2) ensure that your Java & OS-level keystore has been updated with the Jira certificate correctly.  To do this, try to telnet or cURL from your Hygieia server to the Jira server - failures would indicate a network firewall or security issue.  Secondly, use openssh or Java Keytool to validate your Java keystore for the Jira certificate presence; also be sure to add the certificate to your OS-level keystore to ensure no break in communication for Linux/Unix systems (the method for OS-level certificate keystore updating is different between each distribution).

Regarding issue 2, see below for an updated/cleaned property file list based on what you have provided me in the text file; please replace your property file with the fixed one below (update with your credentials, etc.):

215738861 @aryasunny , Thank you for following-up.  The proxy configuration noted within this property file is not Jira specific necessarily; if you have a proxy, you must fill out the proxy configuration section of the properties (currently, the JiraFeatureCollector does not implement system environment configuration for proxy, i.e., HTTP_PROXY).

Regarding your specific error, if you do not have an authentication proxy, your Jira property configuration for the proxy-specific settings should be the following (assuming a proxy IP):

``` properties
# Jira Connection Details - Proxy is NOT just a 'Jira specific proxy' - this is your global enterprise proxy
feature.jiraProxyUrl=http://192.168.1.1
feature.jiraProxyPort=4000
```

column2:
This pull request is the culmination of a 4 week development effort to build a product dashboard to display pipeline health across multiple teams. While this is the major feature delivered by this PR, there are also numerous enhancements and bug fixes, including:
## Enhancements
- Ability to create a product dashboard
- Enhance list view to improve filtering and make product dashboards visually distinct
- Ability to add/remove a team to a product dashboard
- Ability reorder the team rows in a product dashboard via drag and drop
- Ability to view pipeline health (i.e Quality) summary metrics for each team on the product dashboard
- Ability to view commit details for a given pipeline stage
- Ability to view quality details for a given team row
- New API to allow pushing of commits to Hygieia via GitHub webhooks
- New API to allow pushing of build data
- New API to allow pushing of binary artifacts
- New API to allow pushing of deploy data
- New API to allow pushing of quality data
- New API to allow pushing of test result data
- Introduction of a client-side database (Dexie) to reduce the amount data transferred from server to client on every request
## Bug fixes
- Fixes #265 by simplifying and improving the UI gulp build process
- Fixes #113 by creating a global config object in the UI to allow command line args to bypass defaults
- Fixes #275 by upgrading to the latest version of the Chartist library and fixing the existing charts accordingly
- Fixes #170 and #274 via creation of new Chartist plugin

---

You can view, comment on, or merge this pull request online at:

  https://github.com/capitalone/Hygieia/pull/328

Commit Summary
-   allow users to reorder teams on product dashboard
-   default modal to show close button
-   split data processing logic into multiple files
-   Changed how we are pulling mapped names by fetching widget options, shoving them into a case insensitive tree map and using that. Not elegant, but not sure of a better way. The widget options has everything forced to lowercase by the UI before persistence. Also added null safety to pipeline service in case an environment isn't mapped. The treemap doesn't handle nulls for the get.
-   Merge branch 'hygieia-2' of https://github.com/singlestone/Hygieia into hygieia-2
-   catch less errors
-   pmd cleanup
-   Adding comments throughout.
-   More comments around the event listeners. Removed the suppression PMD errors on EnvironmentComponentEventListener as well.
-   prevent js error on initial product dashboard load
-   Merge branch 'hygieia-2' of https://github.com/singlestone/Hygieia into hygieia-2
-   add new form group directive to enable easier implementation of consistent validation throughout the framework. updated existing validations
-   validation message when missing dashboard title
-   change stage cells to show two std deviations in the +- part
-   Simple test for the method on Dashboard that fetches the environment mappings. This exposed a bug when the pipeline isn't configured. Fixed said NPE case.
-   allow dashboard to scroll horizontally
-   Merge branch 'hygieia-2' of https://github.com/singlestone/Hygieia into hygieia-2
-   show std deviation even if it's 0
-   double std deviation before calculating minutes. this way a 50 sec std deviation will show as +-1 min instead of 0
-   rename quality detail
-   Creates pipeline if pipeline doesn't exist.
-   Merge branch 'hygieia-2' of https://github.com/singlestone/Hygieia into hygieia-2
-   refactor product data methods to services
-   added url as reference for Dexie versioning
-   Merge remote-tracking branch 'upstream/hygieia-2.0' into hygieia-2
-   Removed duplicate dependency declaration to resolve maven warning messages.

column11:
183373172 @BeenaMP - I believe the error is related to your build env,potentially your JAVA install.  The error is a connectivity issue between maven and the repo to download the plugins.  If you google "sun.security.validator.ValidatorEx
on: PKIX path building failed: sun.security.provider.certpath.SunCertPathBuilderException: unable to find valid certification path to requested target"  you will find a bunch of hits related to this error, you will have to sift through them to fix your env.

column5: Need help running JIRA collector
column11: 220381172 @jimzucker , Not including the Jira certificate would cause problems, but not this one; I would expect it to throw x509 or PKIX Certificate errors at the Java runtime level. You will need that installed to your Java keystore regardless, however. Just to check my theory, can you try to cURL an authenticated Jira API request to your Jira implementation from your computer? I believe that your command should ultimately look like this: ``` bash # 1) This will give the HTTP code response back; it will not return the actual message: curl --cacert /path/to/your/jira/cert.pem -I -X GET --header "Content-Type: application/json" https://$JIRA_USER:$JIRA_PASS@stratengllc.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/VALIDSTORY-12 # You may need to include the following parameter flag if your Jira certificate is signed using TLS: --tlsv1 # 2) Then, try and run this version of the cURL command; let me know which one worked and which one did not: curl --cacert /path/to/your/jira/cert.pem -I -X GET --header "Authorization: Basic [base64encoded_user:pass]" --header "Content-Type: application/json" https://stratengllc.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/VALIDSTORY-12 # Note: You may also have to included your proxy authorization header explicitly if behind an auth-proxy. Here is the parameter syntax to add to the above calls: --header "Proxy-Authorization: Basic [base64encoded_user:pass]" ``` It is worth mentioning that I also had trouble authenticating using the second option which uses an explicit authorization header. The issue was related to Mac's implementation of base64, which seems to add something invisible to the ASCII result; after re-encoding with a different tool, I received valid base64. I would suggest re-validating your base64 _not_ using the base64 encoder on Mac. If that gets denied for the same HTTP 401 error you were seeing in Hygieia, this is a large problem of your implementation of Jira not allowing for basic authentication. You would ultimately have 2 options at that point: 1) Contact your Jira admin and ask them to enable _nosso_ option of authentication; 2) Update the JiraFeatureCollector to use token-based authentication (token or OAuth2.0). The latter may be the only option. Please let me know how this goes for you. **_EDIT:**_ _For grammatical errors..._ amp5208 220402038 Thanks this strategy worked. The real issue was I was passing emailaddress:password, seems the API requires you use the real userid, email does not work! I will update the file with a good error message and submit it… On May 19, 2016, at 9:36 AM, Arnold Pelka > wrote: Not including the Jira certificate would cause problems, but not this one; I would expect it to throw x509 or PKIX Certificate errors at the Java runtime level. Thank you for your patience and contribution!! amp5208 220623892 For those that come here after the merged fix is implemented, it is important to note that the "ghost" `\n` return carriage that is included in a base64 encoded string on a Mac is avoidable easily by using the Mac implementation of `echo` correctly. Instead of the following command: ``` bash echo username:password | base64 ``` ... Use this command: ``` bash echo -n username:password | base64 ``` The `-n` option explicitly tells the Mac implementation of echo to not print the trailing new line character. amp5208 182667503 Using the clear text password for api key or the actual ali key Regards, Keyur On Feb 10, 2016, at 7:25 PM, Jim Zucker > wrote: Hi, I have been trying to get the JIRA connector to work but I can't figure out why I get a 401 error. Please advise if any progress... tonyvilliams 216956475 @tonyvilliams , Sorry to hear you are also having this issue.. @jimzucker or @tonyvilliams : Just to validate, are you able to run the collectors _without_ using Docker? 😕 e.g.: ``` bash java -jar jira-feature-collector.jar --spring.config.name=jira-feature-collector --spring.config.location=$PROPERTY_PATH/jira-feature-collector.properties ``` If you have already validated the following, I start to think this is related to Docker: - Jira credentials are accurate and have permissions to read from all projects - Jira implementation is within a non-restricted region to your Hygieia implementation - Jira public certificate has been added to the Java keystore - The following properties have been configured based on your Jira implementation: ``` bash feature.jiraIssueTypeId=Story feature.jiraSprintDataFieldName=customfield_10000 feature.jiraEpicIdFieldName=customfield_10001 ``` amp5208 220065862 @amp5208 I am testing now in Eclipse, so I think that takes docker out of the picture. Reviewing today, it looks like my base64 creation of my id and password is adding a '\n' ! I am going to add a bit of code to trim this to make it more resilient.. jimzucker 220118338 @jimzucker , Thank you for discovering this: And also thank you in advance for the contribution 👍 ! @tabladrum : Please review @jimzucker's contribution once it comes it; I expect a one or two line change for the string trimming. Also, label this issue a `Bug`; @jimzucker is going to be contributing the fix. @jimzucker : Other than this, have we answered your configuration question? Can this issue be closed after your impending code contribution? amp5208 220128677 @amp5208 lets keep this open until I get the darn thing running.. jimzucker 220142208 @amp5208 the /n was a problem but I fixed that and I still get a 401 error, line 249 gets the exceptions, any hints on how to debug this? I verified: 1. Userid/passwd - I copied them from the debugger, with the /n removed they are OK now 2. I taste the url in the browser: https://stratengllc.atlassian.net/rest/api/latest/project ![screenshot 2016-05-18 13 04 48](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/14372687/15373213/4daecd92-1cf9-11e6-8e56-bb3ed9dfda2d.png) jimzucker 220162075 hmm... that line of code is resolving your authorization header and request body against Jira's API using the Jira SDK, "claiming" the response, treating it almost like a promise. The only thing that would cause an HTTP 401: Unauthorized response here would be if your credentials are still not being mapped properly. Have you tried debugging that `client` variable to expose your message header information? I believe the problem is how you are establishing your authentication (i.e., what is being transformed and read from your property config), or your Jira implementation does not allow basic authentication (username:password). Have you verified your Jira authentication capabilities with your Jira admin? amp5208 220166344 @amp5208 I stepped into the factory.createWithBasicHttpAuthentication to verify my credentials are OK and the URL is the correct https url.. I think I need a way to verify credentials are OK in the contractor JiraDataFactoryImpl so that we can give a clear error at that time. I dont know the JIRA apis, do you have a suggestion ? jimzucker 220169521 @amp5208 I saw a thread about installing the JIRA cert in the java keystore, that is what I think is wrong, researching it now... jimzucker 220179517 @amp5208 no luck, I put this code in the constructor to ensure ids are correct, I think it has to do with certs or something, I haven't been able to figure it out yet.. any pointers? jiraServerUri = new URI("https://stratengllc.atlassian.net"); client = factory.createWithBasicHttpAuthentication(jiraServerUri, "xxxx", "xxx"); jimzucker 220381172 @jimzucker , Not including the Jira certificate would cause problems, but not this one; I would expect it to throw x509 or PKIX Certificate errors at the Java runtime level. You will need that installed to your Java keystore regardless, however. Just to check my theory, can you try to cURL an authenticated Jira API request to your Jira implementation from your computer? I believe that your command should ultimately look like this: ``` bash # 1) This will give the HTTP code response back; it will not return the actual message: curl --cacert /path/to/your/jira/cert.pem -I -X GET --header "Content-Type: application/json" https://$JIRA_USER:$JIRA_PASS@stratengllc.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/VALIDSTORY-12 # You may need to include the following parameter flag if your Jira certificate is signed using TLS: --tlsv1 # 2) Then, try and run this version of the cURL command; let me know which one worked and which one did not: curl --cacert /path/to/your/jira/cert.pem -I -X GET --header "Authorization: Basic [base64encoded_user:pass]" --header "Content-Type: application/json" https://stratengllc.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/VALIDSTORY-12 # Note: You may also have to included your proxy authorization header explicitly if behind an auth-proxy. Here is the parameter syntax to add to the above calls: --header "Proxy-Authorization: Basic [base64encoded_user:pass]" ``` It is worth mentioning that I also had trouble authenticating using the second option which uses an explicit authorization header. The issue was related to Mac's implementation of base64, which seems to add something invisible to the ASCII result; after re-encoding with a different tool, I received valid base64. I would suggest re-validating your base64 _not_ using the base64 encoder on Mac. If that gets denied for the same HTTP 401 error you were seeing in Hygieia, this is a large problem of your implementation of Jira not allowing for basic authentication. You would ultimately have 2 options at that point: 1) Contact your Jira admin and ask them to enable _nosso_ option of authentication; 2) Update the JiraFeatureCollector to use token-based authentication (token or OAuth2.0). The latter may be the only option. Please let me know how this goes for you. **_EDIT:**_ _For grammatical errors..._ amp5208 220402038 Thanks this strategy worked. The real issue was I was passing emailaddress:password, seems the API requires you use the real userid, email does not work! Here is the parameter syntax to add to the above calls: --header "Proxy-Authorization: Basic [base64encoded_user:pass]" It is worth mentioning that I also had trouble authenticating using the second option which uses an explicit authorization header. The issue was related to Mac's implementation of base64, which seems to add something invisible to the ASCII result. I would suggest re-validating your base64 not use the base64 encoder on Mac. If that gets denied for the same HTTP 401 error you were seeing in Hygieia, this is a large problem of your implementation of Jira not allowing for basic authentication. You would ultimately have 2 options at that point: 1) Contact your Jira admin and ask them to enable nosso option of authentication; 2) Update the JiraFeatureCollector to use token-based authentication (token or OAuth2.0). The latter may be the only option. Please let me know how this goes for you. — You are receiving this because you were mentioned. Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHubhttps://github.com/capitalone/Hygieia/issues/326#issuecomment-220381172 jimzucker 220408662 see pull request #581 jimzucker 220450450 Reviewing PR now. Thank you for your patience and contribution!! amp5208 220623892 For those that come here after the merged fix is implemented, it is important to note that the "ghost" `\n` return carriage that is included in a base64 encoded string on a Mac is avoidable easily by using the Mac implementation of `echo` correctly. Instead of the following command: ``` bash echo username:password | base64 ``` ... Use this command: ``` bash echo -n username:password | base64 ``` The `-n` option explicitly tells the Mac implementation of echo to not print the trailing new line character. amp5208

column2:
This commit adds containers for chat-ops and sonar.  It also modified the poms so you can do mvn docker:build from the root.  

To make it easier for people to download the project I have added containers for test versions of sonar & a jenkins to provide test data to drive the sonar and cucumber collectors.  Longer term we can use these containers to enhance the automated testing of these collectors in the the travis build. 

Note there is an older pull request for #169, I think this should be obsolete now with this commit.

Here are the issues addressed that can be closed with this pull:
#306 - Updated version of jacoco to make it compatible with Sonar Reference
#305 - Added container for Sonar
#239 - Created containers to provide examples for sonar & cucumber
#227 - added container for chat-ops
#169 - Updated docs for docker / docker-compose, changed build to handle docker:build target in the root pom
- cleaned up pom formats with new plugins for docker  
- TODO: today creating the containers is optional, we should consider making part of the package target  
- Note: Disalbed one test for full urls in the .md files, as I wanted to explain how to test the GIT collector using the Hygieia url

Here is a screenshot of how it looks with the demo data once this is merged and you follow the instructions in the Setup doc.

![screenshot 2016-02-09 10 39 48](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/14372687/12927162/86a35720-cf1b-11e5-9808-652efffd78e3.png)

When the pageSize default is exceeded, the resulting payload can take longer than the default socket timeout of 20000ms.  Adjusting this default would help with the larger datasets coming back from jira.

The result of the default is a timeout exception:

`
No result was available from Jira unexpectedly - defaulting to blank response. The reason for this fault is the following:java.net.SocketTimeoutException
`
column5: jira-feature-collector: Allow for a custom timeout for large datasets
column11: 181908163 @xeon22 , Actually, this would obviously be preferable. However, the collector is now using the JRJC. To my knowledge, the newest version of the JRJC does not have a timeout setting override. If you know of an override option for this, outside of overriding the entire class, please let me know, and I will gladly update. amp5208 195478653 @tabladrum , As mentioned in the above comment, socket timeout overrides are not an option for the Jira collector's JRJC. However, using the default pageSize settings, implemented in a previous merge, will resolve this issue. I recommend closing this issue, pending any further questions from @xeon22 . amp5208

column2: When the property is set, it is essentially ignored and the default of 1000 is used.

column2:
Trying to run sonar against our own build to create test/sample data for the dashboard I got an error, to fix this I have to change the version of jacoco.

Error: [ERROR] Failed to execute goal org.sonarsource.scanner.maven:sonar-maven-plugin:3.0.1:sonar (default-cli) on project Hygieia: Unable to read /Users/jaz/work/Hygieia/api/target/jacoco.exec: Incompatible version 1007. -> [Help 1]

I found this on the cloudless site Reference: https://cloudbees.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/205074234-SonarQube-reporting-is-failing-with-a-jacoco-error-Incompatible-version-1007

 This problems comes from an incompatibility in jacoco data produced by your build in version 0.7.5 that SonarQube cannot read with Jacoco 0.7.4. More details:

Issue
StackOverflow
To fix the issue you need to generate your coverage data with Jacoco 0.7.4.

If you are using Apache Maven to produce them replace

 org.jacoco:jacoco-maven-plugin:prepare-agent

``by

 org.jacoco:jacoco-maven-plugin:0.7.4.201502262128:prepare-agent
column5: jacoco 0.7.5 is not compatible with sonar - error 1007

column2:
I have a proposal.  As I was about to add containers for the remaining collectors, I realized the number is growing and everyone may not want to run all of them when the run docker-compose.

Does anyone know a pattern in docker-compose for this, I was unable to find one.

PROPOSAL: I have a proposal that we add an option "DISABLE_COLLECTOR" which can be set on any collector in the docker-cmpose.overrider.yml, if set then the collector will exit but give a very verbose explanation of why it was exited and how to enable it by modifying the docker-compose files.

I will work on this approach unless I get other feedback from the team.

column2:
When running the collector in a container localhost is mapped to http://10.0.2.2 (this is how docker handles the special case of local host it it is natted to that address).

So the URLS from jerkins have to be adjusted to work in your locally browser by changing 10.0.2.2 back to localhost.

Note: the 'view test job' link in the jerkins-cucumber collector works.

![screenshot 2016-02-01 13 27 42](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/14372687/12731909/fc0485dc-c8e7-11e5-90f9-0078992ad3e0.png)

column2:
I accidentally entered an ssh path "git@github.com:capitalone/Hygieia" instead of the https url in one dashboard and they all stopped updating as the collector failed and did not run the other dashboards.

We should consider:
1. Skipping a dashboard on failure and update the others
2. validate in the UI the URL to block the bad input.

The pull request fix that you are referring to allows the use of no proxy, unauthenticated proxy, and an authenticated proxy. Also, there are additional properties required to be set at runtime with the Jira collector, which can be found below (from the README.md): 
# In Jira, general IssueType IDs are associated to various "issue"
# attributes. However, there is one attribute which this collector's
# queries rely on that change between different instantiations of Jira.
# Please provide the name value reference to your instance's IssueType for
# the lowest level of Issues (e.g., "user story") specific to your Jira
# instance.  Note:  You can retrieve your instance's IssueType Name
# listings via the following URI:
# https://[your-jira-domain-name]/rest/api/2/issuetype/.  It is listed as
# attribute "name" in the JSON response.
feature.jiraIssueTypeId=Story
# In Jira, your instance will have its own custom field created for "sprint" or "timebox" details,
# which includes a list of information.  This field allows you to specify that data field for your
# instance of Jira. Note: You can retrieve your instance's sprint data field name
# via the following URI, and look for a package name com.atlassian.greenhopper.service.sprint.Sprint;
# your custom field name describes the values in this field:
# https://[your-jira-domain-name]/rest/api/2/issue/[some-issue-name]
feature.jiraSprintDataFieldName=customfield_10007
# In Jira, your instance will have its own custom field created for "super story" or "epic" back-end ID,
# which includes a list of information.  This field allows you to specify that data field for your instance
# of Jira.  Note:  You can retrieve your instance's epic ID field name via the following URI where your
# queried user story issue has a super issue (e.g., epic) tied to it; your custom field name describes the
# epic value you expect to see, and is the only field that does this for a given issue:
# https://[your-jira-domain-name]/rest/api/2/issue/[some-issue-name]
feature.jiraEpicIdFieldName=customfield_10400
#Core Artifacts
# These arrays of status mappings must be completed in order for custom source system statuses to be providable by
# Hygieia.  Currently, Hygieia only maps to the following 3 status mappings:  to do, doing, and done.  You can find
# all available issue status mappings by going to your instance's version of the following API call:
# http://fake.jira.com/rest/api/2/status/.  Your statuses are listed in the JSON response as "name."
feature.todoStatuses[0]=
feature.doingStatuses[0]=
feature.doneStatuses[0]=

please find below information, hope this helps :

1) while you sign up for the dashboard authentication would create. (creates Instantly)
2) While you start the API the feature, scope are created. (creates Instantly)
3) once you start creating new dashboard dashboard item gets saved . (creates Instantly)
4) saving the widgets, components would created. (creates Instantly)
5) once you run the collector , collector would saved, (it would take time depending upon the corn details ex : 2 minutes or so)
6) once you save any Job (JIRA-COLLECTOR ) in your case, it would create respective collections in collector items get saved in DB. (it would take time depending upon data present for that particular JIRA project depending upon the sprint/issue count ex : 2 minutes or so)

column2:
As mentioned by user @oshingc, there is a bug in the proxy / auth proxy string validation with the Jira collector that needs to be resolved.  If a user has not set a proxy, but their property file has the proxy / auth proxy props set as blank, or not there at all, the tool will currently throw a URI syntax or null pointer exception, as indicated in the following issue:  https://github.com/capitalone/Hygieia/issues/292

This has now been fixed.  Please validate and merge as soon as possible.  I have also wrote additional test cases to cover these scenarios for Jira connections.

column2: I have refactored the entire JiraFeatureCollector based on @jdamick and PMD automated feedback. I have also re-wired the whole transformation and client layer to work with the Jira Atlasssian JRJC library, which ultimately makes heavy use of Jira's domain object model (as opposed to raw HTTP calls and JSON transformation). Please fully review my code and provide feedback. I would also explicitly like feedback in a section that I could not remove all PMD errors on: StoryDataClientImpl.java, line 84-86. Although this section is working and tested and has been refactored as stated above, I cannot reduct overall complexity of the method, because full domain object model translation of hierarchical issues is inherently complex. Note: Please do not fully merge this code until internal functional testing passes early next week. I will post here when functional tests have passed.

column2:
When running mvn clean install package as sudo, I would get an error saying bower install cannot be run with sudo. I had to append --allow-root to the argument in /UI/pom.xml in order to get bower to install and the mvn clean install package to complete successfullly:

``` xml
<execution>
    <id>bower install</id>
    <goals>
        <goal>bower</goal>
    </goals>
    <configuration>
        <arguments>install --allow-root</arguments>      <!-- added --allow-root to argument -->
    </configuration>
</execution>
```

I am trying to run the UI, but I am running into an issue with no error. Builds have succeeded, but when I run "gulp serve" or "gulp serve --local true", it never starts the 'watch' or the 'serve' process which is supposed to bring up the server on localhost:3000. 173130246 @jamesjlee 
Hope you are doing the following steps. I had tough time setting up the dashboard. I deleted dashboarddb in mongodb and recreated them again. 
After this, 

Scaling Agile India
DevOps with Anadi Misra 
1. Build the entire application from root 
   change to directory D:\Hygieia-master 
   execute the following mvn clean install package 

2.change to directory D:\Hygieia-master\api
    execute java -jar target\api.jar --spring.config.name=api --spring.config.location=dashboard.properties
    api monitoring starts

3.change to directory D:\Hygieia-master\UI
    execute gulp serve
    hygieia login page opens at localhost:3000
1. change to directory D:\Hygieia-master\github-scm-collector
   execute java -jar target\github-scm-collector-1.5.0-SNAPSHOT.jar --spring.config.name=application --spring.config.location=application.properties 
   git scm collector monitoring starts
2. change to directory D:\Hygieia-master\jenkins-build-collector
   execute java -jar target\jenkins-build-collector-1.5.0-SNAPSHOT.jar --spring.config.name=application --spring.config.location=application.properties
   jenkins collector starts
3. change to directory D:\Hygieia-master\sonar-codequality-collector
   execute java -jar target\sonar-codequality-collector-1.5.0-SNAPSHOT.jar --spring.config.name=application --spring.config.location=application.properties
   Sonarqube collector starts
4. Signup on localhost:3000 

[property_files.txt](https://github.com/capitalone/Hygieia/files/97136/property_files.txt)

Regards
 javakthar
187397383 Thanks for the help javakthar.

I found the issue. For some reason, the 'serve' command wasn't being run. I had to modify gulpfile and add it in the function runSequence:

gulp.task('build', function(callback) {
    runSequence('clean', ['assets', 'themes', 'fonts', 'js', 'views', 'test-data', 'serve'], 'html', callback);
});
 jamesjlee

There was a recent update with the newest master of the code which requires that you add the following 3 properties to your Jira properties file, depending on your specific Jira instance's configuration: 
. . .
# In Jira, general IssueType IDs are associated to various "issue"
# attributes. However, there is one attribute which this collector's
# queries rely on that change between different instantiations of Jira.
# Please provide a numerical ID reference to your instance's IssueType for
# the lowest level of Issues (e.g., "user story") specific to your Jira
# instance.  Note:  You can retrieve your instance's IssueType ID
# listings via the following URI:  https://[your-jira-domain-name]/rest/api/2/issuetype/
feature.jiraIssueTypeId=7
# In Jira, your instance will have its own custom field created for "sprint" or "timebox" details,
# which includes a list of information.  This field allows you to specify that data field for your
# instance of Jira. Note: You can retrieve your instance's sprint data field name
# via the following URI, and look for a package name com.atlassian.greenhopper.service.sprint.Sprint;
# your custom field name describes the values in this field:
# https://[your-jira-domain-name]/rest/api/2/issue/[some-issue-name]
feature.jiraSprintDataFieldName=customfield_10007
# In Jira, your instance will have its own custom field created for "super story" or "epic" back-end ID,
# which includes a list of information.  This field allows you to specify that data field for your instance
# of Jira.  Note:  You can retrieve your instance's epic ID field name via the following URI where your
# queried user story issue has a super issue (e.g., epic) tied to it; your custom field name describes the
# epic value you expect to see, and is the only field that does this for a given issue:
# https://[your-jira-domain-name]/rest/api/2/issue/[some-issue-name]
feature.jiraEpicIdFieldName=customfield_10400
. . .

column11:
218492727 @manjunath2008 , Please follow up and let me know if you have been successful in validating the following information: https://github.com/capitalone/Hygieia/issues/266#issuecomment-215733119 amp5208 227211031 Hi, Is the Remaining Estimate sums for stories field is the accumulated value per end-user? Or is it across the active sprint ? ashnaa 227211734 I am not able to get all the stories in my active sprint in Hygiea. Any pointers will be of help . ashnaa 227522949 @ashnaa , Thank you for reaching out. The sums are based on accumulated value per team / active sprint. Additionally, a new version of Hygieia's feature widget was released recently that included Kanban/Scrum simultaneous support (https://github.com/capitalone/Hygieia/pull/606). Please pull the latest code and try with the new configuration. Note that the properties required to run the collector have slightly changed - check the updated feature collector README for details. amp5208 270176204 Please use the latest master - a lot of enhancements and fixes have been made to feature widget. tabladrum 172063603 @cfmaley , thank you for reaching out regarding your Jira Feature question. Currently, the "features in progress" content on the FeatureWidget are designed to pull the time-estimate located in the Jira out-of-the-box field called . This is then transformed in the following way so that the numbers are manageable on the display: 
// sEstimate, in seconds, converted to hours, rounded down:
// 8 hours = 1 day; 5 days = 1 week
String hours = "";
long seconds = 0;
try {
       seconds = (long) fields.get("timeestimate");
       hours = Integer.toString((int) (seconds / 3600));
       feature.setsEstimate(TOOLS.sanitizeResponse(hours));
       } catch (Exception e) {
              feature.setsEstimate("0");
       }
Once data is transformed, "in progress" estimates are assumed based on the Jira statusCategory field, which is configured based on your Jira screen's workflow configuration. You must have a statusCategory called "In Progress" - This can be modified by a user with Project Administrative access. The following is the precise MongoDB query being used in code to get this information: 
@Query(value = " {'sTeamID' : ?0 , $and : [{'isDeleted' : 'False'} , {'sState' : 'Active'}] , $or : [{'sStatus' : 'In Progress'} , {'sStatus' : 'Waiting'} , {'sStatus' : 'Impeded'}] , $and : [{'sSprintID' : {$ne : null}} , {'sSprintBeginDate' : {$lte : ?1}} , {'sSprintEndDate' : {$gte : ?1}}]}, $orderby: { 'sStatus' :-1 }", fields = "{'sStatus': 1,'sEstimate' : 1}")
    List getSprintBacklogInProgress(String sTeamID, String currentISODateTime);
Please also note that the newest code in master allows for some custom configuration based on your Jira instance. You should also provided the following property values based on your instance's configuration: 
. . .
# In Jira, general IssueType IDs are associated to various "issue"
# attributes. However, there is one attribute which this collector's
# queries rely on that change between different instantiations of Jira.
# Please provide a numerical ID reference to your instance's IssueType for
# the lowest level of Issues (e.g., "user story") specific to your Jira
# instance.  Note:  You can retrieve your instance's IssueType ID
# listings via the following URI:  https://[your-jira-domain-name]/rest/api/2/issuetype/
feature.jiraIssueTypeId=7
# In Jira, your instance will have its own custom field created for "sprint" or "timebox" details,
# which includes a list of information.  This field allows you to specify that data field for your
# instance of Jira. Note: You can retrieve your instance's sprint data field name
# via the following URI, and look for a package name com.atlassian.greenhopper.service.sprint.Sprint;
# your custom field name describes the values in this field:
# https://[your-jira-domain-name]/rest/api/2/issue/[some-issue-name]
feature.jiraSprintDataFieldName=customfield_10007
# In Jira, your instance will have its own custom field created for "super story" or "epic" back-end ID,
# which includes a list of information.  This field allows you to specify that data field for your instance
# of Jira.  Note:  You can retrieve your instance's epic ID field name via the following URI where your
# queried user story issue has a super issue (e.g., epic) tied to it; your custom field name describes the
# epic value you expect to see, and is the only field that does this for a given issue:
# https://[your-jira-domain-name]/rest/api/2/issue/[some-issue-name]
feature.jiraEpicIdFieldName=customfield_10400
. . .
Please let me know if you have any additional questions and if this issue can be resolved. amp5208 195477808 @tabladrum , This issue can be closed, as it was resolved on a previous merge. @cfmaley, please confirm if you have any open questions related to this issue. amp5208 209353088 Hi All, Can anyone please tell me how is the Done value in Hygieia dashboard is being computed. Thanks & Regards Manjunath manjunath2008 209667297 @manjunath2008 , Thank you for reaching out regarding your question. Currently, the Done value is calculated using either the Detail Estimate value (VersionOne) or the Remaining Estimate value (Jira) summed and rounded-down for any stories mapped to the following statuses: Done, Accepted. Let me know if you need more specific details. amp5208 210585400 Hi, Thanks for the response. I am using Jira collector, I have couple of questions 1) Can you please tell me what information is Jira widget in the dashboard is displaying. 2) What does numeric value above Total, WIP, Done indicate Thanks & Regards Manjunath manjunath2008 213070234 Hi, @amp5208 can you please answer these questions. Thanks & Regards Manjunath.V manjunath2008 215733119 @manjunath2008 , Thank you for following-up. I will answer your questions below: 1. _Can you please tell me what information is Jira widget in the dashboard is displaying._ The feature widget will display Jira's **Remaining Estimate sums for stories** of a given active team/sprint combo selected by the end-user under the following status categories: **All Active (_Total_), In Progress (_WIP_), Done**. As Remaining Estimate is depleted, the sums will also deplete. These are not counts of stories, but instead based on the out-of-the-box Jira burn-down features on issues-type-story. See my answer above for more detail: https://github.com/capitalone/Hygieia/issues/266#issuecomment-209667297 2. _What does numeric value above Total, WIP, Done indicate_ See the answer I provided above. Let me know if you have any further questions. amp5208 218129343 @tabladrum : In Jira feature collector I am facing a problem while passing issueType ID, I have passed strory as IssueType Id in application.prop and I am receiving objects for bug, support and sub-tasks along with story. Could you please share any documentation related to this collector? ghouspasha 218492444 @ghouspasha , Thank you for reaching out. Please make sure that your property is listed precisely as follows: ``` properties feature.jiraIssueTypeId=Story ``` Let me know if you are still seeing issues after ensuring this configuration. All other configuration details are listed in the [README](https://github.com/capitalone/Hygieia/blob/master/jira-feature-collector/README.md), although I will be simplifying the configuration details shortly. amp5208 218492727 @manjunath2008 , Please follow up and let me know if you have been successful in validating the following information: https://github.com/capitalone/Hygieia/issues/266#issuecomment-215733119 amp5208 227211031 Hi, Is the Remaining Estimate sums for stories field is the accumulated value per end-user? Or is it across the active sprint ? ashnaa 227211734 I am not able to get all the stories in my active sprint in Hygiea. Any pointers will be of help . ashnaa 227522949 @ashnaa , Thank you for reaching out. The sums are based on accumulated value per team / active sprint. Additionally, a new version of Hygieia's feature widget was released recently that included Kanban/Scrum simultaneous support (https://github.com/capitalone/Hygieia/pull/606). Please pull the latest code and try with the new configuration. Note that the properties required to run the collector have slightly changed - check the updated feature collector README for details. amp5208 270176204 Please use the latest master - a lot of enhancements and fixes have been made to feature widget. tabladrum

column2: I have beefed up integration/unit testing for the feature widget APIs and the repository Core artifacts used by both API and collectors, proving the issue, and thus proving the fix. I have also ensured that this runs on my machine with the issue resolved with $query. Note: We are still pending functional testing, because we have to stand-up a new CloudFormation to do it - do not fully merge this pull request until after automated functional testing passes.

This is more of an info required request than an issue. The chatops widget probably requires me to define the scope of the Integration. I believe this needs to be done on HipChat. As you had done your integration with HipChat can you please guide me the action that was taken from your end.

As per the readme, I have installed and ran the chatops jar, created a room in Hipchat, saved the integration for the room, and fetched the auth token for the Integration created for the room. Tested the integration by sending message from Integration to Hipchat.

168737590 Yes, i was able to populate the results. I would recommend to review the setup instructions and find if some config is missing in your setup.

Hi,

Request your help in understanding the parameters reported in SonarQube Code Quality widget.
1. In my dashboards, Rules Compliance always shows empty ('-'). Do we need any specific plugin on SonarQube to get this data? In SonarQube server as well, I do not see Rules Compliance metric.
2. Technical Debt shown on Hygieia dashboard and SonarQube dashboard are different. Does Hygieia pick value from any other metric in SonarQube? Because there is a huge difference the values shown in both dashboards. For example, 40 days in SonarQube is shown as 14 days and 1 day 6 hours is shown as 15 hours in Hygieia.
3. What is the source of SECURITY ANALYSIS data? How do we enable it?
4. What is the source of FUNCTIONAL TESTS data? How do we enable it?

Thanks in advance.

I am currently using SonarQube 4.5.1.

166327928 There has been some changes in latest SonarQube on some of the metrics. We will have to revisit some metrics. Some of the metrics are even removed. 

Security analysis: Currently it supports Fortify. We could not publish the collector as it uses some non-Open Source client libraries that comes with Fortify. Fortify's latest release now supports REST and we will rewrite the collector when we start using the latest version. In the mean time, if you are using Fortify and want to use this part of the dashboard, I can give you the collector code and you will have to build it by using those libraries.

Cc: Krishna Kanth B. N.
Subject: Re: [Hygieia] UDeploy Widget always empty (#245)

Can you confirm that UCD collector is running and logging any errors. If you find errors, can you paste them here (PLEASE take out any sensitive information from the JSON that you don't want to share such as internal ip, app name, server identities etc.)

If no error and assuming everything else is ok, I would like to see the output of these UCD api:
1. http://mycompany.ucd.com/rest/deploy/application

this should list all 4 apps you have. Note down the ID of the app that you deployed and note
2. http://mycompay.ucd.com/rest/deploy/application/app_id/environments/false
this should list the environment(s) that your app is deployed. Note down the env id.
3. http://mycompay.ucd.com/rest/deploy/environment/env_id/resources
This should list all the resources (agents, components etc) that are attached to the environment along with their inventory (version etc)
4. http://mycompay.ucd.com/rest/deploy/environment/env_id/noncompliantResources
This should list all the resources that are not compliant with the desired state.

column2:
This enhancement enables the use and running of tests leveraging the embedded MongoDB test packages when an authenticated proxy is required.  This will also work with existing, non-authenticated proxy settings, as the logic for that option will run independent of the logic for authenticated proxies.

I also updated the Setup.md readme to include explicit instructions for how to configure both an authenticated and non-authenticated proxy.
column5: Enabled authenticated proxy configuration for embedded MongoDB tests
column11:
165869677 I'll fix the exception case, the formatting issues and resubmit a commit again.
the removal of scope "test" is actually fixing a runtime issue with VersionOneFeatureCollector, stopping it from actually running.  If you build on your machine with that change, you will see that you will now get the expected "$query" error that i am ultimately fixing.  It is required for that fix.
 amp5208
165875338 I have just committed the requested changes.  @jdamick , Please review and let me know if anything further should be done regarding the embedded mongodb proxy authentication enhancement
 amp5208
165899790 I see what you mean - i'm swallowing the exception instead of handling it before it ever happens.  I'll recommit next week with the changes you have suggested.  Thanks again for the input!
 amp5208
166333750 I have submitted some changes to the committed embedded MongoDB test case which check for authenticated proxy user info content, based on feedback from @jdamick .  I have left one catch for malformed exceptions, which does not entirely swallow the exception, as it prints a log of important information, but i have removed the swallowing NPE.  instead, i replaced this with a double-IF block that uses the tokenizer's built-in boolean check to see if more tokens are available before actually setting them.  this should cover for the use case that the username is blank (assumes then that password is also blank), and if the username is filled but the password is blank.  both cases will skip then to the proxy-only (non-auth) section.

Let me know if you have any remaining issues and i would be happy to fix them.
 amp5208
166336958 thanks
 jdamick
165598126 I can make those modifications; however, please note, as Hygieia is currently written in master will not work with an authenticated proxy - this fix does resolve the issue, but I can make it pull out the username password from the default proxy variable strings.

Please do not close this PR, as I can commit an update directly to this PR.

Thank you for the feedback!
 amp5208
165845523 I have pushed an update to this commit which utilizes the feedback that you provided, @jdamick .  Please review and let me know if you have any additional thoughts or concerns.  I also added a pom fix that was causing an issue to VersionOneFeatureCollector that @tabladrum / @amitmawkin saw the other day, and fixed a method declaration issue with the Core's Component's class (using a 'replace' instead of a 'put', which also performs a replace action).
 amp5208
165859805 @softwareklinic, can you confirm if the updated changes in this pull request will negatively/positively affect a *.pac proxy script, as you have noted as a concern in an earlier pull request?
 amp5208
165868987 pac files aren't used, this only for env variables.
 jdamick
165869677 I'll fix the exception case, the formatting issues and resubmit a commit again.
the removal of scope "test" is actually fixing a runtime issue with VersionOneFeatureCollector, stopping it from actually running.  If you build on your machine with that change, you will see that you will now get the expected "$query" error that i am ultimately fixing.  It is required for that fix.
 amp5208
165875338 I have just committed the requested changes.  @jdamick , Please review and let me know if anything further should be done regarding the embedded mongodb proxy authentication enhancement
 amp5208
165899790 I see what you mean - i'm swallowing the exception instead of handling it before it ever happens.  I'll recommit next week with the changes you have suggested.  Thanks again for the input!

I have left one catch for malformed exceptions, which does not entirely swallow the exception, as it prints a log of important information, but i have removed the swallowing NPE.  instead, i replaced this with a double-IF block that uses the tokenizer's built-in boolean check to see if more tokens are available before actually setting them.  this should cover for the use case that the username is blank (assumes then that password is also blank), and if the username is filled but the password is blank.  both cases will skip then to the proxy-only (non-auth) section.

column2:
VersionOne collector is pulling data from version one everytime and every call. Because of which data duplicate and huge amount of data is getting inserted into the database. The correct behaviour should be to check for existing data. If data is already their into hygieia db then skip the insertion.
Please suggest. Does anyone facing this kind of issue. Any work around it ?
column5: VersionOne Collector Issue - Pulling data on every call and duplicate the records into mongodb

column2:
Current version of Hygieia does not allow for running tests (and thus building) via Maven from behind an authenticated proxy.  This update includes the ability for code to be fully built/tested/run from behind a corporate authentication proxy.  This will also allow for non-authenticated proxies to still be used as per normal.

Also, I updated the Setup readme to clearly indicate how a developer should configure a local proxy if they need to, given this enhancement.
column5: Added capability for tests to run behind an authenticated corporate proxy
column11:
165568333 The HTTP/S_PROXY variables should look like:

```
HTTP_PROXY=http://<id>:<passwd>@proxy.somewhere:80
```

So we shouldnt added HTTP_AUTHxxx, etc. as this breaks users and is non-standard.
 jdamick
165568579 Some of use auto proxy scripts… would that work as well?

From: jdamick <notifications@github.com<mailto:notifications@github.com>>
Reply-To: capitalone/Hygieia <reply@reply.github.com<mailto:reply@reply.github.com>>
Date: Thursday, December 17, 2015 at 2:07 PM
To: capitalone/Hygieia <Hygieia@noreply.github.com<mailto:Hygieia@noreply.github.com>>
Subject: Re: [Hygieia] Added capability for tests to run behind an authenticated corporate proxy (#230)

The HTTP/S_PROXY variables should look like:

HTTP_PROXY=http://<id>:<passwd>@proxy.somewhere:80

So we shouldnt added HTTP_AUTHxxx, etc. as this breaks users..

—
Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHubhttps://github.com/capitalone/Hygieia/pull/230#issuecomment-165568333.
 softwareklinic
165569763 Can you give an example of an "auto proxy script"?
 jdamick
165574815 Are you referring to a proxy host running a .pac file?  if so, your .pac file should still run given the existing proxy logic, as the httpauth-user/pass variables will not even be added to the default authentication set by java.net as long as those system variables are not set.

Please confirm if this works for your use case.

column5: Containers for the collectors
column11:
165276383 Absolutely, it makes perfect sense.

We were discussing during the team meeting today about the same,, since looks like in the current state of affairs, the dashboard can track
1 Branch of code… for any given project at this point… now if we want to track 2-3 branches of the same project… or 2-3 projects… with 3-4 container / branch it would be soon be a mess.

We need to look at 2 things
1.  From infrastructure perspective – how soon we can have the env up and running
2.  How do we manage/design it for future – since soon you will see lot of people adapting this tool and then how do you make this manageable for complex corporate applications.

We were thinking maybe a single container with all collectors + api + ui would be a good option for a given branch.. We can have tracking for any single branch of code up and running quickly…

Let me know your thoughts.

Keyur

column5: Jira feature collector - about the Story.st file
column11:
165277288 Looks like these urls are obsolete... is there any on the new atlassian site? softwareklinic 165500094 Allow me to clarify: You need to replace the "jira.com" host name part of those URLs with your fully qualified Jira host name. I have edited the comment above to reflect this. amp5208 169163696 This issue will be fixed in the newest pull request regarding Feature Widget updates, as you will now be able to specify your Jira instance's custom "user story" issue type ID at deploy-time via properties file amp5208 172060543 @softwareklinic, this issue has now been resolved, as of the most recent update to master. Please pull the newest code and evaluate. Be sure to also update the following 3 property settings based on your Jira instance's configuration: 
. . .
# In Jira, general IssueType IDs are associated to various "issue"
# attributes. However, there is one attribute which this collector's
# queries rely on that change between different instantiations of Jira.
# Please provide a numerical ID reference to your instance's IssueType for
# the lowest level of Issues (e.g., "user story") specific to your Jira
# instance.  Note:  You can retrieve your instance's IssueType ID
# listings via the following URI:  https://[your-jira-domain-name]/rest/api/2/issuetype/
feature.jiraIssueTypeId=7
# In Jira, your instance will have its own custom field created for "sprint" or "timebox" details,
# which includes a list of information.  This field allows you to specify that data field for your
# instance of Jira. Note: You can retrieve your instance's sprint data field name
# via the following URI, and look for a package name com.atlassian.greenhopper.service.sprint.Sprint;
# your custom field name describes the values in this field:
# https://[your-jira-domain-name]/rest/api/2/issue/[some-issue-name]
feature.jiraSprintDataFieldName=customfield_10007
# In Jira, your instance will have its own custom field created for "super story" or "epic" back-end ID,
# which includes a list of information.  This field allows you to specify that data field for your instance
# of Jira.  Note:  You can retrieve your instance's epic ID field name via the following URI where your
# queried user story issue has a super issue (e.g., epic) tied to it; your custom field name describes the
# epic value you expect to see, and is the only field that does this for a given issue:
# https://[your-jira-domain-name]/rest/api/2/issue/[some-issue-name]
feature.jiraEpicIdFieldName=customfield_10400
. . .
amp5208 198561341 Closing it. If the issue is seen again, please reopen it. tabladrum 165159325 Thank you for reaching out regarding the Jira feature collector. The “7” issueType signifies a “story” type issue in Jira. This should be limiting results only to stories. Sample valid query for demonstrative purposes: [YOUR JIRA FQDN]/rest/api/2/search?jql=updatedDate%3E%3D%272015-12-1%27+AND+issueType%3D%277%27+ORDER+BY+updated The following are API descriptions for issue types 1-9: - [YOUR JIRA FQDN]/rest/api/2/issuetype/1 - [YOUR JIRA FQDN]/rest/api/2/issuetype/2 - [YOUR JIRA FQDN]/rest/api/2/issuetype/3 - [YOUR JIRA FQDN]/rest/api/2/issuetype/4 - [YOUR JIRA FQDN]/rest/api/2/issuetype/5 - [YOUR JIRA FQDN]/rest/api/2/issuetype/6 - [YOUR JIRA FQDN]/rest/api/2/issuetype/7 - [YOUR JIRA FQDN]/rest/api/2/issuetype/8 - [YOUR JIRA FQDN]/rest/api/2/issuetype/9 Please let me know if you have any additional questions amp5208 165277288 Looks like these urls are obsolete... is there any on the new atlassian site? softwareklinic 165500094 Allow me to clarify: You need to replace the "jira.com" host name part of those URLs with your fully qualified Jira host name. I have edited the comment above to reflect this. amp5208 169163696 This issue will be fixed in the newest pull request regarding Feature Widget updates, as you will now be able to specify your Jira instance's custom "user story" issue type ID at deploy-time via properties file amp5208 172060543 @softwareklinic, this issue has now been resolved, as of the most recent update to master. Please pull the newest code and evaluate. Be sure to also update the following 3 property settings based on your Jira instance's configuration: 
. . .
# In Jira, general IssueType IDs are associated to various "issue"
# attributes. However, there is one attribute which this collector's
# queries rely on that change between different instantiations of Jira.
# Please provide a numerical ID reference to your instance's IssueType for
# the lowest level of Issues (e.g., "user story") specific to your Jira
# instance.  Note:  You can retrieve your instance's IssueType ID
# listings via the following URI:  https://[your-jira-domain-name]/rest/api/2/issuetype/
feature.jiraIssueTypeId=7
# In Jira, your instance will have its own custom field created for "sprint" or "timebox" details,
# which includes a list of information.  This field allows you to specify that data field for your
# instance of Jira. Note: You can retrieve your instance's sprint data field name
# via the following URI, and look for a package name com.atlassian.greenhopper.service.sprint.Sprint;
# your custom field name describes the values in this field:
# https://[your-jira-domain-name]/rest/api/2/issue/[some-issue-name]
feature.jiraSprintDataFieldName=customfield_10007
# In Jira, your instance will have its own custom field created for "super story" or "epic" back-end ID,
# which includes a list of information.  This field allows you to specify that data field for your instance
# of Jira.  Note:  You can retrieve your instance's epic ID field name via the following URI where your
# queried user story issue has a super issue (e.g., epic) tied to it; your custom field name describes the
# epic value you expect to see, and is the only field that does this for a given issue:
# https://[your-jira-domain-name]/rest/api/2/issue/[some-issue-name]
feature.jiraEpicIdFieldName=customfield_10400
. . .
amp5208 198561341 Closing it. If the issue is seen again, please reopen it. tabladrum

206945783 BINGO.... Thanks a lot. Its working now.
The problem was it was referring to another db. 

Configuration was
#Database Name 
spring.data.mongodb.database=dashboardb

And i changed to 
#Database Name 
dbname=dashboardb

It worked fine.

163775832 That fixed it thanks softwareklinic.  Changed 3 methods from private to protected.

```
protected void log(String marker, long start) {
    log(marker, start, null);
}

protected void log(String text, long start, Integer count) {
    long end = System.currentTimeMillis();
    String elapsed = ((end - start) / 1000) + "s";
    String token2 = "";
    String token3;
    if (count == null) {
        token3 = StringUtils.leftPad(elapsed, 30 - text.length() );
    } else {
        String countStr = count.toString();
        token2 = StringUtils.leftPad(countStr, 20 - text.length() );
        token3 = StringUtils.leftPad(elapsed, 10 );
    }
    LOG.info(text + token2 + token3);
}

protected void logBanner(String instanceUrl) {
    LOG.info("------------------------------");
    LOG.info(instanceUrl);
    LOG.info("------------------------------");
```
